definitions: large plain building or group of buildings used to house soldiers
examples: The new recruits were assigned to barrack number twelve
Soldiers returned to their barracks after evening drill

definitions: large aggressive tropical fish with sharp teeth and elongated body
examples: The diver spotted a barracuda swimming near the coral reef
Barracudas can grow up to six feet in length

definitions: concentrated artillery fire directed at a specific area or target
rapid overwhelming outpouring of things coming in quick succession
examples: The enemy positions faced a heavy artillery barrage at dawn
Artillery units maintained a continuous barrage for three hours
She faced a barrage of questions from the reporters
The company received a barrage of complaints after the announcement
